rank.}) 18... Nxe7 19. Rxd8+ Rxd8 20. bxc3 Nd5 21. Nxd5 Bxd5 $11 {Once again,
the endgame is harmless for Black. In exchange for the pawn, he has active
pieces and a compact pawn structure. The c4-square will soon be occupied by
the bishop. If you want to be confident in such positions, I recommend that
you defend this endgame (and the one arising after 18.bxc3) against the
computer.} *

