It turns out that taking the pawn is impossible since after} 16. Qxc7 $2 Qxc7
17. Rxc7 Nfd5 $17 {White is in troulbe. This evaluation is justified by the
following possible lines:} 18. Rxb7 ({After} 18. Rcc1 Nxa4 $17 {[%cal Gd5c3,
Gb7b5,Gb5b4] Black's advantage is close to winning. It's not clear what White
will do after ...Ndc3 followed by the march of the b-pawn.}) 18... Nc3 19. Rxb6
Nxd1 $17 {White does not have any compensation for the exchange.}) 16... Bd5
$11 {with a repetition to follow.} *

