light-squared bishop).} Nd7 {[%cal Gd7c5] A thematic reaction. Ideally, Black
wants to take on c5 with the knight. From the c5-square, the knight has good
central control and supports the advance of the central pawns.} 10. Bxe7 Qxe7
11. b4 $5 {A very logical move. Since Black is statically better, White should
opt for drastic measures.} ({Dubious is} 11. Nbd2 $6 e5 12. Ne1 Nxc5 $17 {
This position occurred in the game ½-½ (66) Gelfand, B (2734)-Fressinet, L  
