{White is the best way of meeting 6.b3?} 6... dxc4 7. bxc4 c5 {Remember this
thematic reaction against the setups based on b2-b3. Regardless of what White
does, he will end up with an inferior pawn structure. Nevertheless, the strong
Catalan bishop usually manages to balance the chances.} 8. O-O {This is the
main move.} cxd4 9. Nxd4 {This is a typical Catalan structure. In return for
the weak c4-pawn, White enjoys a lasting pressure along the diagonal h1-a8.
These two factors usually balance each other and the position remains equal.
Here, Black's most precise continuation is} Qb6 {[%cal Gf8d8] Preventing Bb2
and freeing the d8-square for the rook. White has tried many options but Black
is doing fine everywhere.} *

